pageContext.claim: ““The President has until September 30th to give this aid to Ukraine. He gets it out on September 11th., 3 weeks before the deadline. So, we give our ally aid, and Joe Biden is not investigated. Remember that, they get the aid and we get nothing in return.”
pageContext.analysis: Testimony suggests that although the fiscal year ends on Sept. 30, the money would have needed to be sent to Ukraine by Sept. 15 to meet congressional requirements or else it would have been lost. This is again a problem of Trump's own making, because he ordered the hold in early July, even though the Defense Department certified in June that Ukraine had met anti-corruption thresholds.
